    "title": {
        "rendered": "We Are All Hezbollah"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p>The hashtag <strong>#We_Are_All_Hezbollah</strong> is currently gaining momentum on social media, primarily promoted by Hezbollah supporters and sympathizers. This dangerous trend seeks to legitimize and glorify Hezbollah, a group officially recognized as a terrorist organization by Israel, the U.S., and many other countries. Hezbollah is responsible for countless acts of terror, including attacks on civilians and efforts to destabilize the region through violence and extremism.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The hashtag attempts to frame Hezbollah as a &#8220;resistance&#8221; group, when in reality, it is a terrorist organization with the explicit goal of destroying Israel and spreading chaos throughout the Middle East. By using <strong>#We_Are_All_Hezbollah</strong>, supporters are aligning themselves with an organization that has committed acts of violence and terrorism for decades.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s crucial to remember that promoting or supporting a terrorist group like Hezbollah not only endorses violence but also perpetuates anti-Israel sentiment and endangers the lives of innocent people. Social media platforms must take responsibility for preventing the spread of dangerous ideologies and ensure that hashtags like <strong>#We_Are_All_Hezbollah</strong> are not used to glorify terrorism.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By standing against this hashtag, we stand for peace, security, and the fight against terrorism.</p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
    "excerpt": {
        "rendered": "<p>The hashtag #We_Are_All_<a  href=\"/hezbollah\">Hezbollah</a> glorifies a terrorist group, spreading dangerous anti-<a  href=\"https://iron-swords.co.il/t/israel/\">Israel</a> sentiment and supporting violent extremism globally.</p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
